      "message": "Suggestion #1: it might be less error prone to override Map\u0027s get() method with the new behavior instead of having a separate method, which the programmer might forget to use at the callsite.\n\nSuggestion #2: Do not set missing keys with the default value, because we\u0027ll lose the information of which keys were explicitly added. Instead, simply return the default if the key is absent.\n\n  get(key: K): V | undefined {\n    if (!this.has(key)) {\n      return this.defaultValueFn();\n    }\n    return super.get(key);\n  }",
